entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think i am pretty good at it i think i am pretty effective at it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was probably two days ago it was my girlfriend and it was about her lack of consideration

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i felt frustrated

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h a situation which i wished i could handle differently i eh in my later years i would say eh i do not have many regrets in my younger years i used to be snubbed by people and i would keep my mouth shut and i would not say anything i would not express my displeasure of their actions or their behavior i would just keep my mouth closed and internalize my feelings i have learned that that is so wrong and so in the probably the last fifteen to twenty years i have made it a point to vocalize my displeasure with someone is actions right away and that takes care of the anger iediately

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: has that gotten you in trouble

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes it it depends what you mean by trouble i think eh all the way around once you take the beginning the beginning to the end it diffuses trouble rather than prolongs or protracts the trouble

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that makes sense tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: going back it would be to not to pursue medicine like my father wanted we argued at length for many months and years about this and finally i prevailed and i did not go to i did not go that route but that was probably the most difficult period in my life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: there was a time when i wished i could erase a female interactions girlfriends and and their betrayals but now i realize that keeping those memories make me who i am today and and dealing with them defines who i am today

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my parents are deceased i had very good relationships with my parents i am very thankful for that even though my father was somewhat of a hard handed and draconian person we came to an understanding well before he died and my brothers i get along great with my younger brother but my older brother has issues he has psychological issues and they they continue to plague him and to affect me also just just knowing that he is going through turmoil

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i guess i really do not cope with it because he is clinically depressed and he has suicidal tendencies and he is not working he is very highly educated and he well he does not talk to me and his family is very abusive towards him it is an not a happy relationship for his family

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: you know i would have to say my father my father is my hero he is my model he is my archetype for what a man should be he is he was unimpeachably honest and kind yet on the other hand he was he had high expectations of me and my two brothers

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: eh usually once my head hits the pillow i am dead asleep like a log but lately i have been having just last night i could not sleep i woke up at two and i have a feeling it is because of a diagnosis of cancer that i received one month ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: xxx i with my own personal methods of handling stress i i am okay i am probably ninety percent okay that ten percent comes from eh an unsuredness about the future about whether i will survive this or not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not really

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel down

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: never

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: never

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh i was either surfing or snowboarding or rock climbing or mountain biking i always experience joy when i am exercising at a very high level of exertion

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: funny jovial intelligent a perfectionist
